      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;gamepublisherdeveloper&#34;&gt;Game/Publisher/Developer&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;7 Days To Die, The Fun Pimps/Telltale Publishing, The Fun Pimps&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;first-look&#34;&gt;First Look&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My first impression wasn&amp;rsquo;t great. The graphics didn&amp;rsquo;t do much to grab my attention right away.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;trailer&#34;&gt;Trailer&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share; fullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/kikTJaVBank?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;my-reaction&#34;&gt;My Reaction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;What won me over was the map size, it&amp;rsquo;s massive. The game ran very smoothly, movement felt fluid and responsive. The performance held up well throughout. My only real complaint was the graphics; it&amp;rsquo;s not the prettiest game out there. Even so, I went ahead and bought 7 Days to Die.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
